WEBVTT

1
00:00:13.714 --> 00:00:14.994
- No.
- Can't leave him alive.

2
00:00:15.048 --> 00:00:17.540
Please go. I'll finish it.

3
00:00:18.018 --> 00:00:20.317
This is between us.

4
00:00:22.923 --> 00:00:24.803
Do it quickly. I'll
be waiting outside.

5
00:00:26.927 --> 00:00:29.897
Hey. what happened to you? I
went out front and you were gone.

6
00:00:30.097 --> 00:00:32.259
<i>There were police. Is it done?</i>

7
00:00:32.432 --> 00:00:34.560
Yes. He's dead.

8
00:00:34.801 --> 00:00:36.599
Call Ellie.

9
00:00:38.038 --> 00:00:39.939
<i>- Hello?</i>
- Hey. it's me.

10
00:00:40.173 --> 00:00:43.166
It's about Tom. It's urgent.

11
00:00:47.214 --> 00:00:49.376
I could lose my
license for this. go to jail.

12
00:00:49.583 --> 00:00:51.449
- You owe me.
- Why aren't we at a hospital?

13
00:00:51.685 --> 00:00:53.916
- He could die.
- He cannot die.

14
00:00:54.121 --> 00:00:56.352
I'm gonna need
supplies. proper tools.

15
00:00:58.091 --> 00:01:00.458
Steven. hey. It's me.
Listen. your boat...

16
00:01:00.961 --> 00:01:03.260
Is it still sitting empty
or did you find a buyer?

17
00:01:03.463 --> 00:01:04.897
He's lost too much blood.

18
00:01:08.902 --> 00:01:12.464
You're a fed. LIZ: He is
responsible for Meera's death.

19
00:01:12.706 --> 00:01:15.266
You were her CI. You said if
I found the man responsible...

20
00:01:15.475 --> 00:01:17.515
I thought you would arrest him.
- I will.

21
00:01:17.711 --> 00:01:20.977
I just need you to babysit for a
little while until I get some info.

22
00:01:27.854 --> 00:01:31.222
Let's get this straight. I did
not save you because I care.

23
00:01:31.425 --> 00:01:34.725
I saved you because
you have intel on Berlin.

24
00:01:35.662 --> 00:01:37.927
I want a name.

25
00:01:39.099 --> 00:01:41.261
- You bitch.
- Oh. I don't know. Tom.

26
00:01:41.468 --> 00:01:44.131
From where I'm sitting.
you look like the bitch to me.

27
00:01:44.404 --> 00:01:47.238
You spied on others?
This what you do?

28
00:01:47.441 --> 00:01:49.433
- I don't remember.
- I want a name. What bank?

29
00:01:49.643 --> 00:01:52.977
Monarch Douglas in Warsaw.
It's where Berlin keeps his money.

30
00:01:53.180 --> 00:01:55.479
What about accounts.
names of shell companies?

31
00:01:55.983 --> 00:01:59.147
Did you murder Jolene
Parker? What about Reddington?

32
00:01:59.386 --> 00:02:00.911
- I don't know.
- What do you know?

33
00:02:01.121 --> 00:02:04.421
- I told you I don't know!
- What do you know about Reddington?!

34
00:02:04.625 --> 00:02:06.958
Stop asking me. I don't know!

35
00:02:07.160 --> 00:02:11.256
When you're convinced I have
nothing left to offer. what then?

36
00:02:11.465 --> 00:02:14.833
I asked you a question.
Gina Zanetakos.

37
00:02:15.035 --> 00:02:18.472
Because you know when this is
over. you're gonna have to kill me. right?

38
00:02:19.473 --> 00:02:22.307
How often did you communicate
with Berlin. his associates?

39
00:02:22.509 --> 00:02:26.412
Tell me about the guests at our wedding. If
you want Ellie to look at that infection...

40
00:02:26.613 --> 00:02:28.172
you have to answer my question.

41
00:02:28.415 --> 00:02:31.214
- I need a doctor!
- I need a name!

42
00:02:31.551 --> 00:02:35.545
- What about the adoption?
- Isn't that what married people do?

43
00:02:36.023 --> 00:02:41.121
You know. all this time. you never
asked me if I ever really loved you.

44
00:02:41.862 --> 00:02:43.956
Because I know the answer.

45
00:02:45.232 --> 00:02:47.428
I don't think you do.

46
00:02:48.201 --> 00:02:51.365
You told me if I gave you
Berlin that you would let me go.

47
00:02:51.571 --> 00:02:57.033
I knew the second you brought me down
you had no intention of letting me leave.

48
00:03:00.547 --> 00:03:01.981
So here's the deal. Liz.

49
00:03:02.182 --> 00:03:05.050
You're gonna do whatever
you're gonna do. You always have.

50
00:03:07.387 --> 00:03:09.982
Just do me one favor.

51
00:03:12.259 --> 00:03:16.026
Look me in the
eyes when you do it.

52
00:03:25.005 --> 00:03:27.873
Your daughter told me
your name is Milos Kirchhoff.

53
00:03:29.242 --> 00:03:30.870
All these years.
Mr. Kirchhoff...

54
00:03:31.078 --> 00:03:34.412
you've believed with the blackest of
hearts that I murdered your daughter.

55
00:03:34.614 --> 00:03:36.583
And yet here she is.

56
00:03:37.551 --> 00:03:39.349
The story was wrong. Milos.

57
00:03:39.553 --> 00:03:41.385
Please enlighten me.

58
00:03:41.588 --> 00:03:44.752
What were you told
and who did the telling?

59
00:03:46.860 --> 00:03:49.022
It was in '91.

60
00:03:49.763 --> 00:03:53.063
The Soviet Union
was falling apart.

61
00:03:53.266 --> 00:03:57.362
A small group of us.
members of the Politburo...

62
00:03:57.571 --> 00:04:02.100
the military. KGB. Stasi...

63
00:04:02.309 --> 00:04:06.644
we had a plan to push
back the progressives...

64
00:04:06.880 --> 00:04:10.373
to stem the tide.

65
00:04:10.584 --> 00:04:17.457
<i>We were meeting and
discussing strategy when a bomb...</i>

66
00:04:20.660 --> 00:04:21.958
The Kursk bombing.

67
00:04:22.162 --> 00:04:28.159
Fifteen men were killed
and with them. our resistance.

68
00:04:28.401 --> 00:04:32.236
Rumors began that the
Americans were involved.

69
00:04:32.773 --> 00:04:35.265
One name emerged.

70
00:04:35.475 --> 00:04:36.568
Yours.

71
00:04:36.777 --> 00:04:39.269
You came after my daughter.

72
00:04:39.479 --> 00:04:42.347
You exposed her as a dissident.

73
00:04:42.582 --> 00:04:44.949
She went to jail.

74
00:04:45.585 --> 00:04:49.113
After that. my loyalty
was questioned.

75
00:04:49.322 --> 00:04:51.848
I was exiled to the Gulag...

76
00:04:52.092 --> 00:04:57.554
where one by one her
bones were sent to me.

77
00:04:57.764 --> 00:05:01.257
You fled. You must
have had help. Who?

78
00:05:02.803 --> 00:05:04.795
There was a man.

79
00:05:05.005 --> 00:05:09.340
He said he could protect
me from... From you.

80
00:05:11.278 --> 00:05:17.013
- What was his name?
- I never met him. I don't know.

81
00:05:17.217 --> 00:05:19.948
His people. they called
him The Decembrist.

82
00:05:20.987 --> 00:05:24.151
Please. That's all I know.

83
00:05:29.362 --> 00:05:34.096
You killed my friends. You destroyed
my life once. Isn't that enough?

84
00:05:42.809 --> 00:05:47.179
At some point I may call.
ask for your assistance.

85
00:05:48.315 --> 00:05:51.911
- About what?
- The Decembrist.

86
00:05:55.355 --> 00:05:56.866
We can't let him
walk out of here.

87
00:05:56.890 --> 00:05:58.850
We agreed when this
was over. I'd arrest him.

88
00:05:59.025 --> 00:06:00.305
That was four months ago.

89
00:06:00.493 --> 00:06:02.655
If you turn him in now.
we'll both go to jail.

90
00:06:02.863 --> 00:06:05.128
- I am not a murderer.
- Neither am I.

91
00:06:05.332 --> 00:06:07.733
Look. you don't have
to be the one to do it.

92
00:06:07.934 --> 00:06:10.563
There are people. But he
can't walk out of here alive.

93
00:06:12.239 --> 00:06:14.902
Close that door. Keep him quiet.

94
00:06:33.860 --> 00:06:34.900
Whoa. whoa.

95
00:06:35.061 --> 00:06:39.226
- Easy! Harbor master. Put the gun down.
- I'm gonna need to see some kind of ID.

96
00:06:39.432 --> 00:06:43.927
We got a call. reports
that someone's trespassing.

97
00:06:44.170 --> 00:06:46.730
Yeah. That's why I'm here. FBI.

98
00:06:46.940 --> 00:06:49.409
We're searching for two
fugitives escaped last night.

99
00:06:49.609 --> 00:06:52.272
Cleared the boat but they're
said to be in the area and armed.

100
00:06:52.479 --> 00:06:53.777
My office wasn't contacted.

101
00:06:53.980 --> 00:06:56.381
Bureau would have reached
out. Homeland's running point.

102
00:06:56.583 --> 00:06:59.451
If you do see anything...

103
00:07:02.689 --> 00:07:04.715
- Be careful.
- Yeah. you too.

104
00:07:08.428 --> 00:07:11.091
Dembe. Where is he?

105
00:07:11.698 --> 00:07:13.291
You're working with Berlin?

106
00:07:13.500 --> 00:07:18.131
I need to talk to you about a bombing
in the Soviet Union. Kursk. 1991.

107
00:07:21.841 --> 00:07:24.106
- Fella won't talk!
- Keep pushing him.

108
00:07:24.311 --> 00:07:29.272
I'm telling you. he's more scared
of talking than he is of dying!

109
00:07:29.482 --> 00:07:33.146
- Keep pushing.
- I'm gonna need lunch!

110
00:07:33.353 --> 00:07:36.289
Tuna on rye!
Coleslaw if they have it!

111
00:07:39.125 --> 00:07:42.289
- What the hell is going on?
- We're shaking a few trees.

112
00:07:42.495 --> 00:07:44.123
There's been a development.

113
00:07:44.331 --> 00:07:48.268
It seems Berlin is merely a pawn
who's been tragically manipulated.

114
00:07:48.468 --> 00:07:51.768
- Manipulated by who?
- That's what Brimley's trying to ascertain.

115
00:07:51.972 --> 00:07:53.804
Berlin killed Meera.
he put Tom in my life.

116
00:07:54.007 --> 00:07:56.533
Every time you have a chance
to stop him. you let him go.

117
00:07:56.776 --> 00:07:58.870
Berlin will be held
accountable for his actions...

118
00:07:59.112 --> 00:08:02.048
after I acquire the name of the
man who set him against me...

119
00:08:02.282 --> 00:08:05.184
a man they call the Decembrist.

120
00:08:05.385 --> 00:08:08.981
If you want to find the one ultimately
responsible for gutting Harold Cooper...

121
00:08:09.189 --> 00:08:13.285
and killing Meera Malik. I
suggest you help me find him.

122
00:08:17.397 --> 00:08:20.333
The man we're looking for
is known as the Decembrist.

123
00:08:20.533 --> 00:08:23.628
His acts contributed to the end
of communism in Eastern Europe.

124
00:08:23.837 --> 00:08:26.329
- How's he connected to Berlin?
- Tried to assassinate him...

125
00:08:26.539 --> 00:08:28.974
during a meeting and
faked his daughter's death.

126
00:08:29.175 --> 00:08:31.508
Berlin's been hunting
Reddington. hunting us.

127
00:08:31.711 --> 00:08:33.577
Reddington wants to
help Berlin get revenge?

128
00:08:33.813 --> 00:08:37.341
That bombing. the men who were killed
were leaders of the Soviet Old Guard.

129
00:08:37.550 --> 00:08:39.849
Think we should be helping
these two settle scores?

130
00:08:40.053 --> 00:08:41.646
Our goal is to take down Berlin.

131
00:08:41.855 --> 00:08:45.292
If that means solving a terrorism
case along the way. I'm fine with that.

132
00:08:45.492 --> 00:08:47.303
- I'll contact the FSB.
- They won't help.

133
00:08:47.327 --> 00:08:50.695
The bombing was considered an
act of patriotism. they never pursued it.

134
00:08:50.897 --> 00:08:52.798
Pull the Russian
reports. crime-lab data.

135
00:08:52.999 --> 00:08:54.865
I want our own analysis.

136
00:09:09.749 --> 00:09:11.308
- They have the bomber's DNA?
- Yes.

137
00:09:11.518 --> 00:09:14.511
The Russian crime lab
reported finding epithelial cells...

138
00:09:14.721 --> 00:09:17.020
on the lip of a coffee
tin found in the debris.

139
00:09:17.223 --> 00:09:20.421
How do you know it was the bomber's
DNA? Didn't anyone else like coffee?

140
00:09:20.627 --> 00:09:22.926
The reports ID'd the
explosive device as Semtex...

141
00:09:23.129 --> 00:09:26.258
same explosives a bomber
used to down Pan Am 103...

142
00:09:26.466 --> 00:09:30.335
- by hiding the explosives...
- In a coffee tin. Our guy copied that?

143
00:09:30.537 --> 00:09:32.233
- They have a name?
- Only a DNA profile...

144
00:09:32.439 --> 00:09:35.967
which was useless 20 years ago before
they had a database to run it against.

145
00:09:36.209 --> 00:09:38.906
- But today...
- You found the Decembrist.

146
00:09:40.880 --> 00:09:42.781
Kiryl Morozov.

147
00:09:42.982 --> 00:09:45.349
Twenty years ago. he was
a low-level KGB operative.

148
00:09:45.552 --> 00:09:49.387
- And today?
- One of the most powerful men in Russia.

149
00:09:49.589 --> 00:09:51.217
Hey!

150
00:09:52.659 --> 00:09:54.389
Someone there?

151
00:09:59.599 --> 00:10:01.397
Okay.

152
00:10:11.277 --> 00:10:12.905
Oh. thank God.

153
00:10:14.147 --> 00:10:15.672
Please.

154
00:10:18.251 --> 00:10:21.449
Kiryl Morozov is one of
Putin's most trusted advisers.

155
00:10:21.654 --> 00:10:23.122
The man runs the
Finance Ministry.

156
00:10:23.323 --> 00:10:26.316
And we have reason to believe he's
responsible for the 1991 bombing...

157
00:10:26.526 --> 00:10:30.190
- in Kursk that left...
- Twelve people dead. In Russia.

158
00:10:30.430 --> 00:10:33.764
FBI investigates crimes that happen
in America or against Americans.

159
00:10:33.967 --> 00:10:37.597
Reddington won't give us
Berlin until we give him Morozov.

160
00:10:37.804 --> 00:10:39.534
At the least. we should
question the man.

161
00:10:39.772 --> 00:10:41.172
I'm not sending you to Moscow...

162
00:10:41.407 --> 00:10:43.638
to interrogate a
high-ranking Russian official...

163
00:10:43.843 --> 00:10:47.280
about an act of terror he may or
may not have committed 25 years ago.

164
00:10:47.480 --> 00:10:49.176
If Reddington gets
to Morozov first...

165
00:10:49.415 --> 00:10:51.941
Harold. that's an order.

166
00:10:57.790 --> 00:10:59.952
That's it? You're just
gonna stand down on this?

167
00:11:00.160 --> 00:11:02.527
You heard her.
My hands are tied.

168
00:11:02.729 --> 00:11:06.666
But Reddington has anonymous sources.
I'm sure he'll get that name somehow.

169
00:11:06.866 --> 00:11:11.930
- Won't he. Agent Keen?
- Yes. sir. I'm sure he will.

170
00:11:18.311 --> 00:11:19.540
Tell me you have a name.

171
00:11:19.746 --> 00:11:22.841
I do. but this can't come back
on the task force. Are we clear?

172
00:11:24.250 --> 00:11:26.048
<i>Hold on. I'll be right back.</i>

173
00:11:26.252 --> 00:11:28.847
- What? Everything okay?
- No. everything's not okay.

174
00:11:29.055 --> 00:11:30.079
We got a situation here.

175
00:11:31.090 --> 00:11:33.355
- I'm sorry. I got to go.
- Lizzy. what's going on?

176
00:11:33.560 --> 00:11:38.157
The Decembrist. his real
name is Kiryl Morozov.

177
00:11:38.364 --> 00:11:42.267
- Something's wrong.
- Kiryl Morozov.

178
00:11:50.176 --> 00:11:53.772
- I got a name.
- So it's done?

179
00:11:54.080 --> 00:11:56.709
- No.
- What are you proposing?

180
00:11:56.916 --> 00:11:58.509
A trip to Moscow.

181
00:12:15.201 --> 00:12:17.201
Went out for a smoke. he was here.
- What the hell?

182
00:12:18.238 --> 00:12:20.115
- Homeboy had a gun.
- Are you out of your mind?

183
00:12:20.139 --> 00:12:22.108
- It was him or me.
- He's got blood on him.

184
00:12:22.308 --> 00:12:24.402
- How are we supposed...
- If he doesn't answer...

185
00:12:24.611 --> 00:12:27.410
someone is gonna
come looking for him.

186
00:12:29.115 --> 00:12:31.812
Okay. Here's what we're gonna
do. We're gonna let him go.

187
00:12:32.051 --> 00:12:34.171
- We'll move Tom. SAMOAN:
Let him go? He's gonna talk.

188
00:12:34.254 --> 00:12:37.088
So let him talk. He says
anything. it's his word against mine.

189
00:12:37.290 --> 00:12:39.290
- And he's an informant.
- Look. lady.

190
00:12:39.392 --> 00:12:42.089
This is obviously official
business. I can look the other way.

191
00:12:42.295 --> 00:12:44.161
- You got to kill him.
- No. please! Listen.

192
00:12:44.397 --> 00:12:46.730
Look. if you let this guy
go. he's going to the cops.

193
00:12:46.933 --> 00:12:50.563
When he does. we are all
going to jail. starting with you...

194
00:12:51.037 --> 00:12:53.302
for torture. kidnapping.
wrongful imprisonment...

195
00:12:53.539 --> 00:12:55.940
take your pick. sweetheart.

196
00:12:56.843 --> 00:12:57.936
You got to kill him.

197
00:13:00.747 --> 00:13:03.581
No. I can fix this. I
have a storage unit.

198
00:13:03.783 --> 00:13:06.184
We'll wait till dark. We'll
keep him here temporarily...

199
00:13:06.419 --> 00:13:08.513
until we can find ano... No!

200
00:13:08.688 --> 00:13:10.408
It's better this
way. Let him do it.

201
00:13:10.490 --> 00:13:12.015
Get off me! Get
your hands off me!

202
00:13:14.994 --> 00:13:18.294
Tom. no! Tom. stop!

203
00:13:20.066 --> 00:13:22.968
- Aah!
- Next one goes in your chest.

204
00:13:24.437 --> 00:13:26.963
Tom. let him go!

205
00:13:36.349 --> 00:13:38.375
I think maybe you
should call Mr. Kaplan.

206
00:13:49.896 --> 00:13:52.229
Vadim. Mercury City Tower.

207
00:13:52.465 --> 00:13:55.663
<i>Kiryl Morozov is paranoid
and well protected.</i>

208
00:13:55.868 --> 00:14:00.499
He has no clear weakness for women
or drink. However. like any politician...

209
00:14:00.707 --> 00:14:05.372
he does have an unending
need to hide his ill-gotten gains.

210
00:14:05.611 --> 00:14:06.635
The diamonds.

211
00:14:06.846 --> 00:14:10.715
Which he buys and sells through your
broker at Mercury City Tower in Moscow.

212
00:14:10.917 --> 00:14:14.319
<i>There was a friendly and rather
convenient diamond heist this morning.</i>

213
00:14:14.520 --> 00:14:16.421
<i>When Morozov learns
the broker's been hit...</i>

214
00:14:16.656 --> 00:14:19.125
<i>he'll insist on a meeting
to assess his exposure.</i>

215
00:14:19.325 --> 00:14:21.226
When he does.
we'll be there waiting.

216
00:14:21.861 --> 00:14:24.160
Milos. focus.

217
00:14:24.364 --> 00:14:30.531
I've made Morozov millions and
he's the one who set all this in motion?

218
00:14:30.737 --> 00:14:32.763
The meeting at Mercury
Tower. when it happens...

219
00:14:33.005 --> 00:14:35.873
it'll happen fast
before the MUR arrives.

220
00:14:40.279 --> 00:14:43.147
My people will be ready.

221
00:14:57.964 --> 00:14:59.865
Who are you? What do you want?

222
00:15:00.066 --> 00:15:01.967
I am retribution.

223
00:15:02.201 --> 00:15:04.241
I don't know what
you're talking about.

224
00:15:04.370 --> 00:15:05.736
Kursk.

225
00:15:08.541 --> 00:15:10.737
- Milos?
- The bombing. my daughter...

226
00:15:10.943 --> 00:15:14.402
- all of it brings us here.
- I did what I was told. Aah.

227
00:15:14.580 --> 00:15:18.745
- You're not the Decembrist.
- It was the American. It was him.

228
00:15:21.421 --> 00:15:24.482
- They gave the order.
- What people?

229
00:15:24.724 --> 00:15:25.919
I can't say.

230
00:15:28.628 --> 00:15:30.688
Who is the Decembrist?

231
00:15:33.499 --> 00:15:34.592
Fitch.

232
00:15:36.068 --> 00:15:39.698
His name is Alan Fitch.

233
00:15:41.908 --> 00:15:44.810
- Milos. this you cannot do.
- Give me one reason.

234
00:15:45.011 --> 00:15:47.276
- Because he's mine.
- Yours? He gave the orders...

235
00:15:47.480 --> 00:15:49.711
discredited you and
you want to protect him?

236
00:15:49.916 --> 00:15:52.977
- This is not for you to do.
- But I will.

237
00:15:53.419 --> 00:15:56.287
Alan Fitch is dead.

238
00:15:56.489 --> 00:15:58.117
Call the florist.

239
00:15:59.459 --> 00:16:01.587
The joint chiefs want
another forward base.

240
00:16:01.794 --> 00:16:04.229
That will only happen if
we can convince Islamabad.

241
00:16:04.430 --> 00:16:09.266
Which is unlikely. It will happen if we
tether it to foreign military investment.

242
00:16:09.469 --> 00:16:11.768
Alan?

243
00:16:11.971 --> 00:16:14.031
Sir. will you make the call?

244
00:16:23.349 --> 00:16:25.511
A little early in the day.
don't you think. Ray?

245
00:16:25.751 --> 00:16:28.118
I'm still on Moscow time.

246
00:16:29.288 --> 00:16:34.124
Just got back from calling on an
old friend of yours. Kiryl Morozov.

247
00:16:34.327 --> 00:16:37.297
You met with the
Russian finance minister?

248
00:16:37.497 --> 00:16:42.333
- To what end?
- To his end as it turned out. Drink?

249
00:16:42.535 --> 00:16:45.562
The finance minister
of Russia is dead.

250
00:16:45.805 --> 00:16:50.004
If a single word of this gets out. if
anyone suspects we sanctioned it...

251
00:16:50.209 --> 00:16:52.075
I didn't sanction anything.
- Damn it.

252
00:16:52.311 --> 00:16:55.076
Your team discovers Morozov
was behind the Kursk bombing...

253
00:16:55.314 --> 00:16:58.284
and 18 hours later. he's
dead? Reddington is behind this.

254
00:16:58.484 --> 00:17:01.545
Reddington called an hour ago.
He believes Fitch's life is in danger.

255
00:17:01.787 --> 00:17:03.847
Did Reddington
bother to tell you...

256
00:17:04.056 --> 00:17:07.720
why Berlin is suddenly
interested in killing Alan Fitch?

257
00:17:07.927 --> 00:17:10.988
He believes he's the one who
orchestrated the Kursk bombing.

258
00:17:11.197 --> 00:17:14.929
Are you accusing the assistant
director of National Intelligence...

259
00:17:15.167 --> 00:17:17.329
- of being a terrorist?
- We need to bring him in.

260
00:17:17.537 --> 00:17:19.403
Alan Fitch is not your concern.

261
00:17:19.605 --> 00:17:25.237
I'll contact the secretary of Homeland
Security and have the situation handled.

262
00:17:25.444 --> 00:17:27.524
- Ray. will you listen?
- We had an agreement.

263
00:17:27.613 --> 00:17:29.309
- Yes.
- I don't go after you...

264
00:17:29.515 --> 00:17:32.849
- you don't come after me.
- I know the terms. Ray.

265
00:17:33.052 --> 00:17:37.683
- But Berlin predates it.
- You ordered the bombing in Kursk.

266
00:17:37.890 --> 00:17:39.518
Then you pinned it on me.

267
00:17:39.725 --> 00:17:42.388
You blamed me for
killing his daughter.

268
00:17:42.595 --> 00:17:47.932
Some years ago. a copy of this photo was
left on the corpse of an associate of mine.

269
00:17:48.134 --> 00:17:52.071
Taking it as a warning. I traced the
girl to a man they call the Stewmaker.

270
00:17:52.271 --> 00:17:54.706
<i>He told me a
story about the girl.</i>

271
00:17:54.907 --> 00:17:57.706
<i>She was sent to him by
a man she'd never met.</i>

272
00:17:57.910 --> 00:18:00.072
<i>She was in trouble.
needed to disappear...</i>

273
00:18:00.279 --> 00:18:04.216
<i>so he took her photo. put it in
a locket and sent it to her father.</i>

274
00:18:04.417 --> 00:18:07.285
All those years spent
searching for the man...

275
00:18:07.486 --> 00:18:11.082
who supposedly murdered
his daughter. and it was you.

276
00:18:11.290 --> 00:18:14.089
You sat here in
this very room...

277
00:18:14.293 --> 00:18:20.494
and pretended you had no idea who
Berlin was or why he was coming for me.

278
00:18:20.733 --> 00:18:24.932
He was coming. Alan.
because you sent him.

279
00:18:26.272 --> 00:18:28.639
I sent a lot of guys.

280
00:18:28.874 --> 00:18:31.366
You and I were not on the
best of terms at the time.

281
00:18:31.744 --> 00:18:35.181
And since you're playing the innocent
victim in all this. let me remind you...

282
00:18:35.414 --> 00:18:38.145
you stole some very
damaging information about us...

283
00:18:38.384 --> 00:18:40.012
when you disappeared.

284
00:18:40.252 --> 00:18:43.745
- You violated our agreement.
- No.

285
00:18:43.956 --> 00:18:45.015
I honored it.

286
00:18:45.257 --> 00:18:48.489
I got the others to hold
off but Milos Kirchhoff...

287
00:18:48.694 --> 00:18:51.687
Berlin. whatever the
hell name he's using...

288
00:18:51.931 --> 00:18:54.093
he chewed through the leash.

289
00:18:54.300 --> 00:18:55.495
I couldn't stop him.

290
00:18:56.268 --> 00:18:59.534
Well. now your dog is
tracking a new scent. yours.

291
00:18:59.772 --> 00:19:02.139
And there's nothing I
can do about that. Alan.

292
00:19:02.341 --> 00:19:06.335
I have my people looking for him
but Berlin has gone into the wind.

293
00:19:06.545 --> 00:19:08.912
And he's coming for you.

294
00:19:10.850 --> 00:19:13.410
You have no allies in my group.

295
00:19:13.619 --> 00:19:15.281
Without me to protect you...

296
00:19:15.488 --> 00:19:19.220
they'll take you down and they'll
let the chips fall where they may.

297
00:19:20.059 --> 00:19:23.996
So this is as much your
problem as it is mine.

298
00:19:26.432 --> 00:19:29.527
ODNI has credible intel that there
might be an attempt on your life.

299
00:19:29.735 --> 00:19:31.704
- What did they say?
- Still waiting to hear.

300
00:19:31.937 --> 00:19:35.339
They want to move you to
Fort McNair to do a full briefing.

301
00:19:35.541 --> 00:19:39.706
Deputy Fitch. Homeland Security.
We need you to come with us.

302
00:19:41.814 --> 00:19:44.079
Guardian's en route.
Delivery on schedule.

303
00:19:54.060 --> 00:19:56.029
Our office has
notified the university.

304
00:19:57.196 --> 00:19:59.665
We have the package.

305
00:20:09.108 --> 00:20:10.701
Contact the D.C. field office.

306
00:20:10.910 --> 00:20:14.176
Get me an update on any
eyewitnesses. satellite footage.

307
00:20:14.380 --> 00:20:16.849
Alan Fitch's abduction
must be on Mossad's radar.

308
00:20:17.049 --> 00:20:20.611
Reach out to your people in
Tel Aviv. And you. talk to him.

309
00:20:22.488 --> 00:20:25.481
Elizabeth. we need to talk. Now.

310
00:20:34.867 --> 00:20:35.891
Tom.

311
00:20:37.303 --> 00:20:42.071
- What?
- You told me Tom is dead. He's not.

312
00:20:43.042 --> 00:20:45.034
Who told you he's alive?

313
00:20:46.579 --> 00:20:51.244
I'm disappointed you haven't felt that
you could trust me enough to tell me this.

314
00:20:54.920 --> 00:20:58.584
Look. okay. I lied. But
I only kept it a secret...

315
00:20:58.758 --> 00:21:00.198
because I know
you want him dead.

316
00:21:00.292 --> 00:21:03.285
You kept it a secret because you
didn't want to admit to yourself...

317
00:21:03.529 --> 00:21:05.020
that you still love him...

318
00:21:05.231 --> 00:21:07.097
that even after
everything he has done...

319
00:21:07.299 --> 00:21:10.667
after how horribly he treated
you. you still can't let him go.

320
00:21:10.903 --> 00:21:13.634
So you're playing house.

321
00:21:13.839 --> 00:21:17.435
I've been using him as a source
and he's been incredibly valuable.

322
00:21:20.446 --> 00:21:23.644
Normally. any intelligence you
could gather from Tom Keen...

323
00:21:23.849 --> 00:21:25.249
would be yesterday's news...

324
00:21:25.451 --> 00:21:28.910
but Berlin has gone to ground and
is likely dependent on former assets...

325
00:21:29.121 --> 00:21:31.556
he used when your
husband was in his employ.

326
00:21:31.757 --> 00:21:35.990
So it seems Tom may
be of some value after all.

327
00:21:36.195 --> 00:21:40.291
I need to know everything he can tell
you about Berlin's former safe houses...

328
00:21:40.499 --> 00:21:42.195
former contacts.

329
00:21:42.434 --> 00:21:46.098
All that matters is
finding Alan Fitch.

330
00:21:52.945 --> 00:21:55.972
- This ends now.
- I already gave you Berlin.

331
00:21:56.182 --> 00:21:58.981
- I told you where to find him.
- Yes. and he disappeared.

332
00:21:59.185 --> 00:22:02.678
- I did everything I could from in here.
- Forget it.

333
00:22:02.888 --> 00:22:05.208
- I already told you...
- And I told you it's the only way.

334
00:22:06.392 --> 00:22:09.226
Take a look. Liz.
This is a problem.

335
00:22:09.461 --> 00:22:14.126
- And time is not on your side.
- I need information. not advice.

336
00:22:14.333 --> 00:22:16.598
We both know that you
are in over your head.

337
00:22:16.802 --> 00:22:20.170
You are not equipped for this.
Liz. because you are not a killer.

338
00:22:20.372 --> 00:22:22.967
It's why I'm still alive and
you've got a corpse there...

339
00:22:23.175 --> 00:22:26.543
that you have done nothing
with. And your bodyguard...

340
00:22:26.745 --> 00:22:29.738
the one that you shot. where
do you think he is right now?

341
00:22:29.982 --> 00:22:31.507
He's getting a gun so he can...

342
00:22:31.717 --> 00:22:33.709
kill me and then
probably kill you too.

343
00:22:33.919 --> 00:22:35.751
Now. I told you there
is a way out of this.

344
00:22:35.988 --> 00:22:42.417
I can give you Berlin and all
you have to do is let me go.

345
00:22:44.763 --> 00:22:46.561
Gosh. he's a popular guy.

346
00:22:49.535 --> 00:22:51.561
I bet somebody's gonna miss him.

347
00:22:51.770 --> 00:22:53.432
Berlin.

348
00:22:58.544 --> 00:23:01.139
<i>- Orenburg six.</i>
- Scorpio.

349
00:23:01.347 --> 00:23:05.045
<i>- That function Is no longer valid.</i>
- Wait. wait. listen.

350
00:23:05.251 --> 00:23:07.743
Tell him Tom Keen wants to talk.

351
00:23:08.454 --> 00:23:12.687
Liz. why would you do this? I
mean. you're risking everything.

352
00:23:12.892 --> 00:23:14.087
To find Berlin.

353
00:23:14.293 --> 00:23:16.373
You're a federal agent
harboring a fugitive.

354
00:23:16.528 --> 00:23:19.657
I mean. worse than that.
you're keeping him captive.

355
00:23:19.865 --> 00:23:22.266
Five hundred cops are out
looking for Fitch right now...

356
00:23:22.468 --> 00:23:25.267
and we're gonna find
him because of this.

357
00:23:29.875 --> 00:23:31.537
<i>I thought you were dead.</i>

358
00:23:31.744 --> 00:23:34.213
- I need you to bring me in.
<i>- No.</i>

359
00:23:34.413 --> 00:23:38.248
- Listen to me. I can help you.
- Well. time has passed.

360
00:23:38.450 --> 00:23:40.544
- Plans have changed.
- I know you have Fitch.

361
00:23:40.753 --> 00:23:42.813
I know everything they
know about your operation.

362
00:23:43.055 --> 00:23:45.889
You're gonna want to hear it
but I'm not telling you anything...

363
00:23:46.091 --> 00:23:47.719
until you bring me in.

364
00:23:49.795 --> 00:23:53.061
Whether he leads us to Fitch
or not. I got to take him in.

365
00:23:53.265 --> 00:23:55.825
Are you hearing me? You
had to know when you told me...

366
00:23:56.068 --> 00:23:58.765
that this is where
it was gonna go.

367
00:23:58.971 --> 00:24:02.999
- Liz. I can't be part of this.
- He's an informant like Reddington.

368
00:24:03.242 --> 00:24:07.304
The difference is you're
not in love with Reddington.

369
00:24:10.716 --> 00:24:12.582
- I got an address.
- Where?

370
00:24:12.785 --> 00:24:14.913
Where? What difference
does it make where?

371
00:24:15.120 --> 00:24:18.420
What? You're gonna follow his lead
to someplace he says Berlin is hiding?

372
00:24:18.624 --> 00:24:21.924
- No. There could be 50 guys waiting.
- That's stupid.

373
00:24:22.127 --> 00:24:25.825
- Hey. shut up. I wasn't asking you.
- You want Berlin or not?

374
00:24:26.031 --> 00:24:29.092
No way I'm gonna let you go in
there. This is a setup. an ambush.

375
00:24:29.735 --> 00:24:30.964
What are you. her boyfriend?

376
00:24:32.938 --> 00:24:34.839
Hey!

377
00:24:35.808 --> 00:24:37.436
What address?

378
00:24:52.458 --> 00:24:56.122
3952 Spalding
Street. Apartment 24.

379
00:24:56.328 --> 00:25:01.460
- Hey. pal. I'm coming for you.
- Good luck with that.

380
00:25:16.849 --> 00:25:18.283
Down!

381
00:25:19.218 --> 00:25:20.777
Target's neutralized.

382
00:25:20.986 --> 00:25:25.082
- I think we have a problem. MAN
3: Clear it out. Let's go. Clear out.

383
00:25:52.117 --> 00:25:54.757
Looks like we're dealing
with a plastic explosive. C4...

384
00:25:54.853 --> 00:25:56.048
approximately 2 kilos.

385
00:25:56.255 --> 00:25:58.520
Sir. the blasting cap's
wired to a receiver.

386
00:25:58.724 --> 00:26:01.036
- We found our detonator.
- Can be detonated remotely.

387
00:26:01.060 --> 00:26:02.426
We need to jam
the frequencies...

388
00:26:02.628 --> 00:26:05.826
- in case this nutjob tries to set it off.
- Then you're gonna disarm it?

389
00:26:06.031 --> 00:26:08.043
We have a vehicle for
controlled detonation.

390
00:26:08.067 --> 00:26:10.127
Should be big enough for
Fitch and one of my men.

391
00:26:10.369 --> 00:26:13.635
Once he's contained. we can attempt
to disassemble and disarm the device.

392
00:26:13.872 --> 00:26:15.583
How long will that
thing take to get here?

393
00:26:15.607 --> 00:26:16.767
Half-hour minimum...

394
00:26:16.842 --> 00:26:20.279
unless you've got another
R.F.-resistant armored box that fits two.

395
00:26:20.479 --> 00:26:23.540
Actually. I think it fits four.

396
00:26:58.784 --> 00:27:00.904
<i>We managed to gain
access to the internals...</i>

397
00:27:01.019 --> 00:27:03.818
trying to circumvent the
keypad. Here's what we got so far.

398
00:27:04.022 --> 00:27:07.117
The Semtex runs along the circumference
of the collar. as you can see.

399
00:27:07.326 --> 00:27:10.262
Encased within that. approximately
14 inches of solid core wire...

400
00:27:10.462 --> 00:27:12.158
connected to a
microprocessor which...

401
00:27:12.397 --> 00:27:14.678
- creates a closed circuit.
- Cut the collar off...

402
00:27:14.800 --> 00:27:16.769
you interrupt the
circuit and bang?

403
00:27:17.803 --> 00:27:20.170
- Then how do we disable it?
- Cautiously.

404
00:27:20.405 --> 00:27:23.000
We need to chip through the
Semtex to see what's underneath...

405
00:27:23.208 --> 00:27:25.302
make sure there aren't
any redundant circuits.

406
00:27:25.511 --> 00:27:28.174
And you can do that
without triggering that thing?

407
00:27:28.413 --> 00:27:30.041
We'll find out. won't we?

408
00:27:31.550 --> 00:27:34.213
Look. I know I
disobeyed a direct...

409
00:27:34.419 --> 00:27:36.479
You found him.
That's all that matters.

410
00:27:36.688 --> 00:27:38.782
- Fill me in.
- We got played. Keen.

411
00:27:38.991 --> 00:27:40.857
I mean. look at
it. Berlin's gone.

412
00:27:41.059 --> 00:27:42.687
- Tom's free.
- He brought us Fitch.

413
00:27:42.928 --> 00:27:47.024
Berlin handed us Fitch on a silver platter
after he had a bomb strapped to his neck.

414
00:27:49.935 --> 00:27:52.461
Look. I've been thinking about
what I said in the car and...

415
00:27:52.671 --> 00:27:55.937
Don't worry about it.
Ressler. I'll tell Cooper.

416
00:28:02.080 --> 00:28:04.640
I understand you're
responsible for finding Fitch.

417
00:28:05.250 --> 00:28:06.843
- About the source...
- Yeah.

418
00:28:07.052 --> 00:28:11.148
- Does he have information about Berlin?
- Yes. we believe he does.

419
00:28:11.356 --> 00:28:15.452
I don't care if your source is confidential
or what promises you've made him.

420
00:28:15.661 --> 00:28:20.599
I want him here. I want him
interrogated and I want his name.

421
00:28:21.366 --> 00:28:24.268
- You must be kidding.
- Do I sound like I'm kidding?

422
00:28:25.571 --> 00:28:29.667
It's Reddington. Her
source is Reddington.

423
00:28:36.915 --> 00:28:39.350
Please excuse my intrusion.

424
00:28:40.719 --> 00:28:44.087
I'm curious. Your father. I assume
he's been trying to reach you.

425
00:28:44.289 --> 00:28:45.552
Has he called?

426
00:28:49.795 --> 00:28:51.730
I thought as much.

427
00:29:10.415 --> 00:29:13.317
<i>Sir. the device has a secondary
detonator built in as a safeguard.</i>

428
00:29:13.552 --> 00:29:15.453
- What kind of safeguard?
<i>- A timer.</i>

429
00:29:15.654 --> 00:29:18.283
Think it was activated when
the receiver broke radio contact.

430
00:29:18.523 --> 00:29:20.001
- How long do you have?
- Unclear.

431
00:29:20.025 --> 00:29:22.654
We see the timing circuit but
no display. Could be a minute...

432
00:29:22.894 --> 00:29:24.123
<i>it could be an hour.</i>

433
00:29:33.739 --> 00:29:36.106
- You're not hungry?
- It's fine.

434
00:29:36.308 --> 00:29:40.404
Let's get you something
else. Huh? Whatever you like.

435
00:29:44.182 --> 00:29:46.913
- I can tell them to go.
- No. I'm the one who should go.

436
00:29:47.119 --> 00:29:50.453
No. no. They make
you uncomfortable.

437
00:29:58.597 --> 00:30:00.065
I'm glad you called.

438
00:30:01.166 --> 00:30:02.998
You're scared.

439
00:30:03.702 --> 00:30:05.170
I am too.

440
00:30:10.509 --> 00:30:13.968
I don't know how
to talk to someone...

441
00:30:15.147 --> 00:30:16.479
like you.

442
00:30:18.450 --> 00:30:21.943
- I really should go.
- No. Please don't.

443
00:30:22.154 --> 00:30:24.623
I know you have your life.

444
00:30:25.090 --> 00:30:28.618
I have no place there. I know.

445
00:30:28.827 --> 00:30:33.822
But I just want you
to stay a little longer.

446
00:30:41.506 --> 00:30:43.475
Hello. Milos.

447
00:30:48.180 --> 00:30:52.379
Thank you. my dear. Passports.
tickets and my eternal gratitude.

448
00:31:04.129 --> 00:31:07.429
The bomb. I need to
know how to stop the bomb.

449
00:31:08.533 --> 00:31:11.401
- I don't know.
- That's the wrong answer.

450
00:31:12.637 --> 00:31:13.935
I'm telling you. I don't...

451
00:31:16.007 --> 00:31:17.839
Think harder.

452
00:31:23.749 --> 00:31:26.344
What's your name. son? - What?

453
00:31:26.551 --> 00:31:28.782
Your name. What is it?

454
00:31:29.654 --> 00:31:32.590
Sir. I need to be
as still as possible.

455
00:31:32.958 --> 00:31:36.861
Any movement. the
vibrations of your voice...

456
00:31:38.597 --> 00:31:40.429
You have a wife?

457
00:31:41.566 --> 00:31:44.798
Kids? That's what
makes it the hardest...

458
00:31:45.036 --> 00:31:46.664
a wife and kids.

459
00:31:48.173 --> 00:31:50.768
I've been in the intelligence
field a long time now.

460
00:31:50.976 --> 00:31:56.438
On my orders. 763 men
and women have died...

461
00:31:57.182 --> 00:31:59.447
in service to their country.

462
00:31:59.684 --> 00:32:03.052
And there wasn't a grieving
wife or mother or husband...

463
00:32:03.255 --> 00:32:06.885
I didn't either call
or visit personally.

464
00:32:07.626 --> 00:32:10.926
Thank them for their sacrifice.

465
00:32:11.129 --> 00:32:14.622
That's what makes it
the hardest. the families.

466
00:32:16.101 --> 00:32:18.263
You can't disarm it. can you?

467
00:32:19.571 --> 00:32:22.268
Sir. I asked you to
be as still as possible.

468
00:32:22.841 --> 00:32:25.640
Seven hundred and sixty-three.

469
00:32:28.513 --> 00:32:30.914
That's more than enough.

470
00:32:31.583 --> 00:32:34.985
I'm not gonna make it 764.

471
00:32:35.487 --> 00:32:37.149
What's your name?

472
00:32:39.024 --> 00:32:42.222
Mike. My name's Mike.

473
00:32:42.427 --> 00:32:44.453
Go home. Mike.

474
00:32:45.230 --> 00:32:47.222
You've done everything you can.

475
00:33:15.961 --> 00:33:17.452
Harold. I know you're listening.

476
00:33:17.662 --> 00:33:19.631
<i>Tell Ray I need to see him.</i>

477
00:33:52.998 --> 00:33:56.196
What a long. strange
trip it's been. Alan.

478
00:33:56.401 --> 00:33:58.563
Listen to me. Ray.

479
00:33:58.803 --> 00:34:02.831
I don't know how much time we
have. so you need to pay attention.

480
00:34:03.041 --> 00:34:04.839
I've been able to
hold everyone off...

481
00:34:05.043 --> 00:34:09.378
convince them that it's in their
best interests to let you live.

482
00:34:09.581 --> 00:34:11.948
But people aren't as
scared as they once were.

483
00:34:12.183 --> 00:34:14.448
Some aren't so sure
you even have it.

484
00:34:15.420 --> 00:34:17.446
Do you have it. Ray?

485
00:34:17.822 --> 00:34:19.313
Do you have the fulcrum?

486
00:34:23.228 --> 00:34:25.026
They're gonna demand proof.

487
00:34:25.964 --> 00:34:28.593
I can't stop this thing. Alan.

488
00:34:29.401 --> 00:34:30.960
I tried.

489
00:34:31.369 --> 00:34:33.065
I can't.

490
00:34:33.271 --> 00:34:36.469
My death will trigger
a series of events.

491
00:34:36.708 --> 00:34:38.734
The moderates were
already outnumbered.

492
00:34:38.944 --> 00:34:42.745
The closer we get to 2017. the
more radicalized they'll become.

493
00:34:42.948 --> 00:34:45.611
Talk to Mitchum and Hobbs.

494
00:34:45.850 --> 00:34:48.410
They might be persuaded.

495
00:34:48.620 --> 00:34:51.146
Jasper sides with the Chinese.

496
00:34:53.091 --> 00:34:55.117
Listen to me.
Ray. This is critical.

497
00:34:55.360 --> 00:34:58.091
I have a safe. Get to it.

498
00:34:58.296 --> 00:35:04.668
The combination. 8-30-44.

499
00:35:04.903 --> 00:35:07.896
- Remember that. Say it back.
- 8-30-44.

500
00:35:08.106 --> 00:35:10.371
8-30-44.

501
00:35:14.446 --> 00:35:16.779
Margaret's birthday.

502
00:35:17.949 --> 00:35:20.680
You've had a wonderful
life together. Alan.

503
00:35:21.620 --> 00:35:25.148
Fifty-one years last month.

504
00:35:28.760 --> 00:35:30.695
The safe.

505
00:35:31.329 --> 00:35:33.298
Yeah. the safe.

506
00:35:34.899 --> 00:35:39.098
It's at St. Petersburg in the
wall on the second floor of...

507
00:35:59.691 --> 00:36:01.489
Untie him.

508
00:36:15.006 --> 00:36:16.201
Thank you.

509
00:37:14.299 --> 00:37:19.533
I remember the parades
from when I was a young boy...

510
00:37:19.738 --> 00:37:22.708
standing by my father...

511
00:37:22.907 --> 00:37:29.143
seeing those trucks that went
by with the rockets and cannons.

512
00:37:29.380 --> 00:37:31.576
Beautiful. Ha-ha-ha.

513
00:37:34.552 --> 00:37:39.252
And all those men
marching as one...

514
00:37:39.457 --> 00:37:43.121
saluting at me as one.

515
00:37:45.029 --> 00:37:49.057
Our soldiers. our nation.

516
00:37:51.636 --> 00:37:55.300
Yuri Gagarin was
the first man in space.

517
00:37:57.075 --> 00:37:59.601
We were so proud.

518
00:39:09.047 --> 00:39:12.745
Your gentleman friend with the
earring said he moved the body.

519
00:39:15.053 --> 00:39:19.047
Mr. Kaplan is with him now.
We're trying to contain the situation.

520
00:39:23.328 --> 00:39:24.728
You should have come to me.

521
00:39:26.064 --> 00:39:28.556
- I didn't need to.
- Look around you. Lizzy.

522
00:39:28.766 --> 00:39:31.531
- We found Fitch because of Tom.
- It wasn't worth it.

523
00:39:31.736 --> 00:39:36.902
Not if the cost was
you here in this...

524
00:39:39.010 --> 00:39:40.706
filth.

525
00:39:44.782 --> 00:39:46.944
I couldn't do it.

526
00:39:47.185 --> 00:39:52.715
I told you I could kill Tom
but after you left. I just...

527
00:39:57.896 --> 00:40:00.798
After all the lies and
everything he did to me...

528
00:40:01.032 --> 00:40:07.597
I told myself I was using
him. that I was finally in control.

529
00:40:12.477 --> 00:40:15.208
When you love someone.
you have no control.

530
00:40:15.413 --> 00:40:17.382
That's what love is...

531
00:40:18.950 --> 00:40:21.181
being powerless.

532
00:40:22.253 --> 00:40:25.052
I don't know what's
wrong with me.

533
00:40:27.091 --> 00:40:29.253
There's nothing wrong with you.

534
00:40:31.062 --> 00:40:33.258
There's nothing wrong with you.

535
00:40:33.431 --> 00:40:37.061
<i>♪ But can you move and shake? ♪</i>

536
00:40:38.436 --> 00:40:44.603
<i>♪ Are you a hitman or a fake? ♪</i>

537
00:40:52.216 --> 00:40:58.087
<i>♪ Are you a hitman or a fake? ♪</i>

538
00:41:05.430 --> 00:41:11.028
<i>♪ Are you a hitman or a fake? ♪</i>

539
00:41:23.247 --> 00:41:25.307
<i>♪ I'll look to higher ground ♪</i>

540
00:41:25.483 --> 00:41:26.883
Do you have it?

541
00:41:27.118 --> 00:41:31.021
<i>♪ And see this
world around you ♪</i>

542
00:41:31.622 --> 00:41:34.854
<i>♪ There'll be no hesitation ♪</i>

543
00:41:38.329 --> 00:41:42.323
<i>♪ There'll be no hesitation ♪</i>

544
00:41:46.004 --> 00:41:47.836
<i>♪ But can you move ♪</i>

545
00:41:48.006 --> 00:41:51.272
You are never to see her again.

546
00:41:51.476 --> 00:41:54.503
<i>♪ Are you a hitman ♪♪</i>

547
00:41:54.679 --> 00:41:56.705
Yeah. I got it.

548
00:41:58.016 --> 00:42:02.147
I don't think you
do. Look at me.

549
00:42:04.856 --> 00:42:09.021
You are never to see her again.

550
00:42:16.200 --> 00:42:20.194
You know. for what it's worth. I spent
four months on that ship chained up...

551
00:42:21.839 --> 00:42:24.240
and I never told her about us.

552
00:42:25.309 --> 00:42:27.574
Not one word.
